gomodel:SYNGO_2622  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: \"Subcellular distribution of ABHD17\"\n- \"FLAG-tagged ABHD17A localized at the plasma membrane, and some populations were distributed in the dendrites as vesicular-like structures and partly colocalized with postsynaptic scaffolding protein Shank in dendritic spines (Fig. 3A).\"\n- \"We then examined the ABHD17A localization using various marker proteins and found that ABHD17A localized mainly on TfR-positive recycling endosomes in the dendritic shafts and spines (Fig. 3B).\". Experimental description: \" Differential subcellular distribution of FLAG-tagged ABHD proteins and Lypla2. Note that some populations of ABHD17A localized at the postsynaptic membranes labeled by pan-Shank antibody (red) in 14 DIV rat hippocampal neurons.\"\n\n- \"The cDNAs of rat ...ABHD17A (NM_001006983), ... ABHD17B (NM_146096), ABHD17C (NM_133722), ...\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099033 replaced by GO:0098944" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2622" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

